Package: hazgrid
Title: Programmable Hazus-Style Hazard and Loss Workflows
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("El", "Cordero", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "33505811+el-cordero@users.noreply.github.com")
Description: Provides transparent, staged, terra-first building hazard and loss
    workflows inspired by Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) Hazus
    methods. The initial implementation supports tsunami depth, velocity, and
    momentum-flux inputs with validated fragility and loss-ratio tables, plus an
    earthquake capacity-spectrum framework using user-supplied hazard rasters
    and validated lookup tables. It is an independent implementation framework
    and does not reproduce official Hazus results without validated inputs and
    lookup tables.
